 Port Elizabeth -  A 28-year-old Uber driver managed to escape unharmed after his Grey Ford Figo was hijacked in Zwide, Port Elizabeth, over the weekend. "This followed after the driver was making a passenger pick up in Sir Grey Street in Zwide at 17:00, on Sunday," described police spokesperson, Captain Andre Beetge. "The two male suspects got into the vehicle and immediately started shooting at the driver. "The driver managed to escape from the vehicle and into a nearby house without being wounded even while the suspects continued shooting at him while he ran away." Capt Beetge said that the suspects then fled the scene with the vehicle. "The vehicle was later found abandoned in Van Der Kemp Street, Zwide at 18:30." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  